131999 | managerclubs5 = [[FK \u017deleznik|\u017deleznik]]\n| manageryears6  = 2000\u20132003 | managerclubs6 = [[Beijing Guoan]] (assistant)\n| manageryears7  = 2004            | managerclubs7 = [[Red Star Belgrade]] (caretaker)\n| manageryears8  = 2004\u20132005 | managerclubs8 = [[Al-Sadd Sports Club|Al-Sadd]] (assistant)\n| manageryears9  = 2006\u20132007 | managerclubs9 = [[FK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]\n| manageryears10 = 2008            | managerclubs10 = [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]]\n| manageryears11 = 2008\u20132010 | managerclubs11 = [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]]\n| manageryears12 = 2010\u20132011 | managerclubs12 = [[Al-Ahli Jeddah|Al-Ahli]]\n| manageryears13 = 2011    | managerclubs13 = [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]]\n| manageryears14 = 2016    | managerclubs14 = [[NK Rudar Velenje|Rudar Velenje]]\n| manageryears15 = 2016   | managerclubs15 = [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]]\n| manageryears16 = 2017\u20132019 |managerclubs16 = [[Thailand national football team|Thailand]]\n| manageryears17 = \n}}\n'''Milovan Rajevac''' (Serbian: \u041c\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d \u0420\u0430\u0458\u0435\u0432\u0430\u0446; born 2 January 1954) is a Serbian [[Manager (association football)|football manager]] and former professional player.\n\n==Playing career==\n{{expand section|date=March 2016}}\nBorn in [[\u010cajetina]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/players/manager?id=122|title=Milovan Rajevac profile|accessdate=15 February 2010|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> Rajevac played as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]], [[Red Star Belgrade]], [[FK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]], [[Lunds BK]], and the [[New York Arrows]] (as \"Mike Rejevac\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/worldcup2010/2010/06/26/2010-06-26_ghana_coach_milovan_rajevac_concerned_about_injuries_entering_world_cup_match_wi.html|title=Ghana coach Milovan Rajevac is concerned about injuries entering World Cup match with United States|accessdate=2 July 2010|date=26 June 2010|author=Filip Bondy and Michael Lewis|publisher=NY Daily News}}</ref><ref name = \"Jerseys\">http://www.nasljerseys.com/MISL/Players/R/Rajevac.Mike.htm</ref>) and [[FK Sloboda U\u017eice|Sloboda U\u017eice]].\n\n==Managerial career==\nRajevac coached a number of club sides in his native Serbia, including [[FK Sloboda U\u017eice|Sloboda U\u017eice]], [[Red Star Belgrade]], [[FK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]] and [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20090305094123/http://www.zerodic.com/autor/fudbal_1945-1992/igraci/igraci_r.htm Stars from Yugoslav First and Second Leagues] at zerodic.com</ref>\n\nHe became [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] manager in August 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ghanafa.org/blackstars/200808/3105.asp|title=Rajevac named new Ghana coach|accessdate=4 May 2009|date=12 August 2008|publisher=Ghana Football Association|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090812060225/http://ghanafa.org/blackstars/200808/3105.asp|archive-date=12 August 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/africa/7556126.stm|title=Serbian coach for Black Stars|accessdate=4 May 2009|date=12 August 2008|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He continued the Black Stars's [[2010 World Cup qualification|qualification campaign]] to [[2010 World Cup]]. In the tournament, they almost reached the semi-final as they narrowly lost to [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] in the quarter-final via [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]].<ref>{{cite news | date=2 July 2013 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2010/jul/02/uruguay-ghana-world-cup-report | title= World Cup 2010: Uruguay make Gyan and Ghana pay the penalty |author= Paul Wilson| work= theguardian.com |publisher=[[The Guardian]] | accessdate=13 December 2013}}</ref> [[File:Milovan Rajevac.jpg|thumb|150px|left|Coach Milovan Rajevac with the Ghana national football team]]\n\nRajevac quit Ghana after the World Cup on 8 September 2010, and took up a position with Saudi Arabian team [[Al-Ahli Saudi FC|Al-Ahli]] a day later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ghanasoccernet.com/2010/09/ex-ghana-coach-rajevac-joins-saudi-side/|title=Ex-Ghana coach Rajevac joins Saudi side|accessdate=11 September 2010|date=9 September 2010|publisher=Ghana Soccernet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110309030654/http://ghanasoccernet.com/2010/09/ex-ghana-coach-rajevac-joins-saudi-side/|archive-date=9 March 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHe left the Saudi club in February 2011 to take up the role as national team coach for [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/sports/soccer/news/_/id/6164168/qatar-hires-milovan-rajevac-coach-team-14|title=Qatar hires Milovan Rajevac as coach|accessdate=27 February 2011|date=27 February 2011|publisher=ESPN}}</ref> He was relieved of duties in August 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dohastadiumplusqatar.com/lazaroni-replaces-rajevac-qatar-coach/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=25 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111125231028/http://www.dohastadiumplusqatar.com/lazaroni-replaces-rajevac-qatar-coach/ |archivedate=25 November 2011 }}</ref>\n\nIn September 2011, Rajevac was one of four managers linked with the Egyptian national team,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/14786943.stm|title=Egypt to choose between Bradley and Rajevac for coach|date=8 September 2011|accessdate=26 June 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> and in February 2014 he was one of four managers linked with the Burkina Faso national team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/31519155|title=Nigerian Stephen Keshi on shortlist for Burkina Faso job|date=18 February 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 June 2016, he was officially appointed as manager of [[NK Rudar Velenje|Rudar Velenje]] in Slovenia.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rtvslo.si/sport/nogomet/na-klopi-rudarja-moz-ki-je-gano-popeljal-v-cetrtfinale-sp-ja/395809|title=Na klopi Rudarja mo\u017e, ki je Gano popeljal v \u010detrtfinale SP-ja|trans-title=Manager, who reached the World Cup quarterfinals with Ghana, will manage Rudar|publisher=[[Radiotelevizija Slovenija]]|date=15 June 2016|accessdate=26 June 2016|language=Slovenian|author=M.R.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://nkrudarvelenje.com/2016/06/15/nk-rudar-velenje-bo-vodil-milovan-rajevac/|title=NK Rudar Velenje bo vodil Milovan Rajevac|accessdate=27 June 2016|language=Slovenian|publisher=[[NK Rudar Velenje]] official website|date=15 June 2016|trans-title=Milovan Rajevac will manage Rudar Velenje}}</ref> However, on 26 June 2016 he was appointed as manager of the [[Algeria national football team|Algerian national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/36636116|title=Ex Ghana coach Milovan Rajevac gets Algeria job|date=26 June 2016|accessdate=26 June 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He resigned from the position in October 2016, after two matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37629477|title=Milovan Rajevac quits as Algeria coach after two games|date=12 October 2016|accessdate=12 October 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, after the resignation of [[Kiatisuk Senamuang]],<ref>{{cite web|language=English|url=http://fathailand.org/news/448|title=Sport Hero Co Ltd's contract to be terminated}}</ref> he had an interview with [[Football Association of Thailand]] and was expected to become the head coach of the [[Thailand national football team]].<ref>{{cite web|language=Thai|work=[[Thai Rath]]|url=http://www.thairath.co.th/content/919805|title=\u0e04\u0e19\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e41\u0e2b\u0e25\u0e30! '\u0e2a\u0e21\u0e22\u0e28' \u0e40\u0e15\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e21\u0e15\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07 '\u0e23\u0e32\u0e40\u0e22\u0e27\u0e31\u0e0a' \u0e04\u0e38\u0e21\u0e44\u0e17\u0e22\u0e40\u0e0b\u0e47\u0e19 1 \u0e1b\u0e35\u0e04\u0e48\u0e32\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e07\u0e40\u0e17\u0e48\u0e32\u0e0b\u0e34\u0e42\u0e01\u0e49|date=22 April 2017|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref> Eventually, he was appointed on one-year deal with an option for another one year by Football Association of Thailand on 26 April 2017.<ref>{{cite web|language=English|url=http://fathailand.org/news/517|title=ANNOUNCEMENT : Milovan Rajevac appointed Thailand national head coach}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|language=Thai|work=[[Matichon]]|url=https://www.matichon.co.th/sport/news_542911|title=\u0e40\u0e1c\u0e22\u0e04\u0e48\u0e32\u0e40\u0e2b\u0e19\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e22\u2019\u0e23\u0e32\u0e40\u0e22\u0e27\u0e31\u0e0a\u2019\u0e2a\u0e39\u0e07\u0e01\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u2019\u0e0b\u0e34\u0e42\u0e01\u0e49\u2019-\u0e40\u0e15\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e21\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e14\u0e34\u0e21\u0e07\u0e32\u0e19\u0e41\u0e23\u0e01\u0e14\u0e39\u0e40\u0e01\u0e21\u2019\u0e40\u0e21\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e17\u0e2d\u0e07\u2019\u0e1f\u0e31\u0e14\u2019\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e19\u0e32\u0e27\u0e35\u2019|date=26 April 2017|accessdate=5 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 February 2018, Football Association of Thailand announced the extension of Rajevac's contract to 2020.<ref>{{cite web|language=Thai|work=[[Thai Rath]]|url=https://www.thairath.co.th/content/1195998|title=\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e49\u0e19\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e14\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e04\u0e2d\u0e22! \u0e2a.\u0e1a\u0e2d\u0e25\u0e08\u0e31\u0e1a '\u0e23\u0e32\u0e40\u0e22\u0e27\u0e31\u0e0a' \u0e15\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e2a\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e0d\u0e32\u0e16\u0e36\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e35 2563|date=5 February 2018|accessdate=5 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe was sacked on 7 January 2019 following a 4\u20131 defeat against [[India national football team|India]] in the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mgronline.com/sport/detail/9620000001844|language=thai|work=[[Manager Online]]|date=2019-01-07|title=\u0e14\u0e48\u0e27\u0e19! \u0e1b\u0e25\u0e14 \"\u0e23\u0e32\u0e40\u0e22\u0e27\u0e31\u0e0a\" \u0e40\u0e0b\u0e48\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e48\u0e32\u0e22\u0e2d\u0e34\u0e19\u0e40\u0e14\u0e35\u0e22\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e14\u0e23\u0e39\u0e1b \u0e15\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07 \"\u0e28\u0e34\u0e23\u0e34\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c\" \u0e04\u0e38\u0e21\u0e41\u0e17\u0e19\u0e0a\u0e31\u0e48\u0e27\u0e04\u0e23\u0e32\u0e27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.khaosod.co.th/sports/news_1920084|work=[[Khao Sod]]|language=thai|title=5 \u0e40\u0e23\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e19\u0e48\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e19\u0e43\u0e08 \u0e2b\u0e25\u0e31\u0e07\u0e40\u0e01\u0e21 \u2018\u0e0a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e07\u0e28\u0e36\u0e01\u2019 \u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e14\u0e47\u0e19\u0e15\u0e01\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e1a \u0e0b\u0e39\u0e0b\u0e39\u0e01\u0e34 \u0e04\u0e31\u0e1e 2018|date=2018-12-06}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Manager===\n'''Thailand'''\n*[[King's Cup]]: [[2017 King's Cup|2017]]<ref>{{cite web|work=Footballghana.com|url=https://footballghana.com/ex-ghana-coach-milovan-rajevac-wins-first-silverware-with-thailand|title=Ex-Ghana coach Milovan Rajevac wins first silverware with Thailand|date=19 July 2017|accessdate=6 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Serbian Footballer of the Year|Serbian Coach of the Year]]: 2010<ref>{{cite web|work=Blic Sport|url=https://sport.blic.rs/fudbal/domaci-fudbal/fss-stankovic-i-rajevac-najbolji-u-2010-godini/jen95r6|title=FSS: Stankovi\u0107 i Rajevac najbolji u 2010. godini|date=23 December 2018|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref>\n*[[CAF Awards|African Coach of the Year]]: 2010<ref>{{cite web|work=Ahram Online|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/6/52/20336/Sports/National-Teams/Serbian-coach-Rajevac-joins-race-for-Egypt-job.aspx|title=Serbian coach Rajevac joins race for Egypt job|date=5 September 2011|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Milovan Rajevac international tournaments\n|list1=\n{{Ghana Squad 2010 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Ghana Squad 2010 World Cup}}\n{{Thailand squad 2019 AFC Asian Cup}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Milovan Rajevac managerial positions\n|list1=\n{{Red Star Belgrade managers}}\n{{FK Vojvodina managers}}\n{{Ghana national football team managers}}\n{{Al-Ahli Saudi FC managers}}\n{{Qatar national football team managers}}\n{{Algeria national football team managers}}\n{{Thailand national football team managers}}\n}}\n{{Football Association of Serbia Coach of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rajevac, Milovan}}\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from \u010cajetina]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav footballers]]\n[[Category:Serbian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak players]]\n[[Category:Red Star Belgrade footballers]]\n[[Category:FK Vojvodina players]]\n[[Category:FK Sloboda U\u017eice players]]\n[[Category:Serbian football managers]]\n[[Category:Red Star Belgrade managers]]\n[[Category:FK Vojvodina managers]]\n[[Category:2010 FIFA World Cup managers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Ghana]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Qatar]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Serbian SuperLiga managers]]\n[[Category:Serbian people of Bosnia and Herzegovina descent]]\n[[Category:Al-Ahli Saudi FC managers]]\n[[Category:Ghana national football team managers]]\n[[Category:Qatar national football team managers]]\n[[Category:FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak managers]]\n[[Category:FK Sloboda U\u017eice managers]]\n[[Category:NK Rudar Velenje managers]]\n[[Category:Serbian expatriates in Slovenia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Slovenia]]\n[[Category:2010 Africa Cup of Nations managers]]\n[[Category:Algeria national football team managers]]\n[[Category:Thailand national football team managers]]\n[[Category:2019 AFC Asian Cup managers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{BLP sources|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name     = Milovan Rajevac\n| image   = Milovan Rajevac 2017 (cropped).jpg\n| caption = {{small|Rajevac coaching [[Thailand national football team|Thailand]] in 2017.}}\n| image_size = 200px\n| fullname       = \n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1954|1|2|df=y}}<ref name = \"Jerseys\"/>\n| birth_place = [[\u010cajetina]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|FPR Yugoslavia]]\n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub    = \n| years1         = 1973\u20131977 | clubs1 = [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]]            | caps1 = 64 | goals1 = 2\n| years2         = 1977\u20131978 | clubs2 = [[Red Star Belgrade]]                     | caps2 = 13 | goals2 = 0\n| years3         = 1979\u20131980 | clubs3 = [[FK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]                | caps3 = 15 | goals3 = 0\n| years4         = 1981\u20131982 | clubs4 = [[New York Arrows]]                       | caps4 = 11 | goals4 = 1\n| years5         = 1982\u20131984 | clubs5 = [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]]            | caps5 = 25 | goals5 = 0\n| years6         = 1984\u20131985 | clubs6 = [[Lunds BK]]                              | caps6 =  | goals6 =\n| years7         = 1985\u20131986 | clubs7 = [[FK Sloboda U\u017eice|Sloboda U\u017eice]]        | caps7 = 3  | goals7 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 1976 | nationalteam1 = [[Yugoslavia national football team|Yugoslavia Olympic]]\n| nationalcaps1  =               | nationalgoals1= \n| manageryears1  = 1989\u20131992 | managerclubs1 = [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]]\n| manageryears2  = 1992\u20131994 | managerclubs2 = KSF Srbija Malm\u00f6\n| manageryears3  = 1994\u20131996 | managerclubs3 = [[FK Sloboda U\u017eice|Sloboda U\u017eice]]\n| manageryears4  = 1996\u20131998 | managerclubs4 = Progres Frankfurt\n| manageryears5  = 1998\u20131999 | managerclubs5 = [[FK \u017deleznik|\u017deleznik]]\n| manageryears6  = 2000\u20132003 | managerclubs6 = [[Beijing Guoan]] (assistant)\n| manageryears7  = 2004            | managerclubs7 = [[Red Star Belgrade]] (caretaker)\n| manageryears8  = 2004\u20132005 | managerclubs8 = [[Al-Sadd Sports Club|Al-Sadd]] (assistant)\n| manageryears9  = 2006\u20132007 | managerclubs9 = [[FK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]\n| manageryears10 = 2008            | managerclubs10 = [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]]\n| manageryears11 = 2008\u20132010 | managerclubs11 = [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]]\n| manageryears12 = 2010\u20132011 | managerclubs12 = [[Al-Ahli Jeddah|Al-Ahli]]\n| manageryears13 = 2011    | managerclubs13 = [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]]\n| manageryears14 = 2016    | managerclubs14 = [[NK Rudar Velenje|Rudar Velenje]]\n| manageryears15 = 2016   | managerclubs15 = [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]]\n| manageryears16 = 2017\u20132019 |managerclubs16 = [[Thailand national football team|Thailand]]\n| manageryears17 = \n}}\n'''Milovan Rajevac''' (Serbian: \u041c\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d \u0420\u0430\u0458\u0435\u0432\u0430\u0446; born 2 January 1954) is a Serbian [[Manager (association football)|football manager]] and former professional player.\n\n==Playing career==\n{{expand section|date=March 2016}}\nBorn in [[\u010cajetina]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/players/manager?id=122|title=Milovan Rajevac profile|accessdate=15 February 2010|publisher=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> Rajevac played as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]], [[Red Star Belgrade]], [[FK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]], [[Lunds BK]], and the [[New York Arrows]] (as \"Mike Rejevac\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/worldcup2010/2010/06/26/2010-06-26_ghana_coach_milovan_rajevac_concerned_about_injuries_entering_world_cup_match_wi.html|title=Ghana coach Milovan Rajevac is concerned about injuries entering World Cup match with United States|accessdate=2 July 2010|date=26 June 2010|author=Filip Bondy and Michael Lewis|publisher=NY Daily News}}</ref><ref name = \"Jerseys\">http://www.nasljerseys.com/MISL/Players/R/Rajevac.Mike.htm</ref>) and [[FK Sloboda U\u017eice|Sloboda U\u017eice]].\n\n==Managerial career==\nRajevac coached a number of club sides in his native Serbia, including [[FK Sloboda U\u017eice|Sloboda U\u017eice]], [[Red Star Belgrade]], [[FK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]] and [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20090305094123/http://www.zerodic.com/autor/fudbal_1945-1992/igraci/igraci_r.htm Stars from Yugoslav First and Second Leagues] at zerodic.com</ref>\n\nHe became [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] manager in August 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ghanafa.org/blackstars/200808/3105.asp|title=Rajevac named new Ghana coach|accessdate=4 May 2009|date=12 August 2008|publisher=Ghana Football Association|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090812060225/http://ghanafa.org/blackstars/200808/3105.asp|archive-date=12 August 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/africa/7556126.stm|title=Serbian coach for Black Stars|accessdate=4 May 2009|date=12 August 2008|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He continued the Black Stars's [[2010 World Cup qualification|qualification campaign]] to [[2010 World Cup]]. In the tournament, they almost reach semi-final as they narrowly lost to [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] in the quarter-final via [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]].<ref>{{cite news | date=2 July 2013 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2010/jul/02/uruguay-ghana-world-cup-report | title= World Cup 2010: Uruguay make Gyan and Ghana pay the penalty |author= Paul Wilson| work= theguardian.com |publisher=[[The Guardian]] | accessdate=13 December 2013}}</ref> [[File:Milovan Rajevac.jpg|thumb|150px|left|Coach Milovan Rajevac with the Ghana national football team]]\n\nRajevac quit Ghana after the World Cup on 8 September 2010, and took up a position with Saudi Arabian team [[Al-Ahli Saudi FC|Al-Ahli]] a day later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ghanasoccernet.com/2010/09/ex-ghana-coach-rajevac-joins-saudi-side/|title=Ex-Ghana coach Rajevac joins Saudi side|accessdate=11 September 2010|date=9 September 2010|publisher=Ghana Soccernet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110309030654/http://ghanasoccernet.com/2010/09/ex-ghana-coach-rajevac-joins-saudi-side/|archive-date=9 March 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHe left the Saudi club in February 2011 to take up the role as national team coach for [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/sports/soccer/news/_/id/6164168/qatar-hires-milovan-rajevac-coach-team-14|title=Qatar hires Milovan Rajevac as coach|accessdate=27 February 2011|date=27 February 2011|publisher=ESPN}}</ref> He was relieved of duties in August 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dohastadiumplusqatar.com/lazaroni-replaces-rajevac-qatar-coach/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=25 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111125231028/http://www.dohastadiumplusqatar.com/lazaroni-replaces-rajevac-qatar-coach/ |archivedate=25 November 2011 }}</ref>\n\nIn September 2011, Rajevac was one of four managers linked with the Egyptian national team,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/14786943.stm|title=Egypt to choose between Bradley and Rajevac for coach|date=8 September 2011|accessdate=26 June 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> and in February 2014 he was one of four managers linked with the Burkina Faso national team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/31519155|title=Nigerian Stephen Keshi on shortlist for Burkina Faso job|date=18 February 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 June 2016, he was officially appointed as manager of [[NK Rudar Velenje|Rudar Velenje]] in Slovenia.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rtvslo.si/sport/nogomet/na-klopi-rudarja-moz-ki-je-gano-popeljal-v-cetrtfinale-sp-ja/395809|title=Na klopi Rudarja mo\u017e, ki je Gano popeljal v \u010detrtfinale SP-ja|trans-title=Manager, who reached the World Cup quarterfinals with Ghana, will manage Rudar|publisher=[[Radiotelevizija Slovenija]]|date=15 June 2016|accessdate=26 June 2016|language=Slovenian|author=M.R.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://nkrudarvelenje.com/2016/06/15/nk-rudar-velenje-bo-vodil-milovan-rajevac/|title=NK Rudar Velenje bo vodil Milovan Rajevac|accessdate=27 June 2016|language=Slovenian|publisher=[[NK Rudar Velenje]] official website|date=15 June 2016|trans-title=Milovan Rajevac will manage Rudar Velenje}}</ref> However, on 26 June 2016 he was appointed as manager of the [[Algeria national football team|Algerian national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/36636116|title=Ex Ghana coach Milovan Rajevac gets Algeria job|date=26 June 2016|accessdate=26 June 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He resigned from the position in October 2016, after two matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37629477|title=Milovan Rajevac quits as Algeria coach after two games|date=12 October 2016|accessdate=12 October 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, after the resignation of [[Kiatisuk Senamuang]],<ref>{{cite web|language=English|url=http://fathailand.org/news/448|title=Sport Hero Co Ltd's contract to be terminated}}</ref> he had an interview with [[Football Association of Thailand]] and was expected to become the head coach of the [[Thailand national football team]].<ref>{{cite web|language=Thai|work=[[Thai Rath]]|url=http://www.thairath.co.th/content/919805|title=\u0e04\u0e19\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e41\u0e2b\u0e25\u0e30! '\u0e2a\u0e21\u0e22\u0e28' \u0e40\u0e15\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e21\u0e15\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07 '\u0e23\u0e32\u0e40\u0e22\u0e27\u0e31\u0e0a' \u0e04\u0e38\u0e21\u0e44\u0e17\u0e22\u0e40\u0e0b\u0e47\u0e19 1 \u0e1b\u0e35\u0e04\u0e48\u0e32\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e07\u0e40\u0e17\u0e48\u0e32\u0e0b\u0e34\u0e42\u0e01\u0e49|date=22 April 2017|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref> Eventually, he was appointed on one-year deal with an option for another one year by Football Association of Thailand on 26 April 2017.<ref>{{cite web|language=English|url=http://fathailand.org/news/517|title=ANNOUNCEMENT : Milovan Rajevac appointed Thailand national head coach}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|language=Thai|work=[[Matichon]]|url=https://www.matichon.co.th/sport/news_542911|title=\u0e40\u0e1c\u0e22\u0e04\u0e48\u0e32\u0e40\u0e2b\u0e19\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e22\u2019\u0e23\u0e32\u0e40\u0e22\u0e27\u0e31\u0e0a\u2019\u0e2a\u0e39\u0e07\u0e01\u0e27\u0e48\u0e32\u2019\u0e0b\u0e34\u0e42\u0e01\u0e49\u2019-\u0e40\u0e15\u0e23\u0e35\u0e22\u0e21\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e14\u0e34\u0e21\u0e07\u0e32\u0e19\u0e41\u0e23\u0e01\u0e14\u0e39\u0e40\u0e01\u0e21\u2019\u0e40\u0e21\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e17\u0e2d\u0e07\u2019\u0e1f\u0e31\u0e14\u2019\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e19\u0e32\u0e27\u0e35\u2019|date=26 April 2017|accessdate=5 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 February 2018, Football Association of Thailand announced the extension of Rajevac's contract to 2020.<ref>{{cite web|language=Thai|work=[[Thai Rath]]|url=https://www.thairath.co.th/content/1195998|title=\u0e2a\u0e34\u0e49\u0e19\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e14\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e04\u0e2d\u0e22! \u0e2a.\u0e1a\u0e2d\u0e25\u0e08\u0e31\u0e1a '\u0e23\u0e32\u0e40\u0e22\u0e27\u0e31\u0e0a' \u0e15\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e2a\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e0d\u0e32\u0e16\u0e36\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e35 2563|date=5 February 2018|accessdate=5 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe was sacked on 7 January 2019 following a 4\u20131 defeat against [[India national football team|India]] in the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mgronline.com/sport/detail/9620000001844|language=thai|work=[[Manager Online]]|date=2019-01-07|title=\u0e14\u0e48\u0e27\u0e19! \u0e1b\u0e25\u0e14 \"\u0e23\u0e32\u0e40\u0e22\u0e27\u0e31\u0e0a\" \u0e40\u0e0b\u0e48\u0e19\u0e1e\u0e48\u0e32\u0e22\u0e2d\u0e34\u0e19\u0e40\u0e14\u0e35\u0e22\u0e2b\u0e21\u0e14\u0e23\u0e39\u0e1b \u0e15\u0e31\u0e49\u0e07 \"\u0e28\u0e34\u0e23\u0e34\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c\" \u0e04\u0e38\u0e21\u0e41\u0e17\u0e19\u0e0a\u0e31\u0e48\u0e27\u0e04\u0e23\u0e32\u0e27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.khaosod.co.th/sports/news_1920084|work=[[Khao Sod]]|language=thai|title=5 \u0e40\u0e23\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e19\u0e48\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e19\u0e43\u0e08 \u0e2b\u0e25\u0e31\u0e07\u0e40\u0e01\u0e21 \u2018\u0e0a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e07\u0e28\u0e36\u0e01\u2019 \u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e14\u0e47\u0e19\u0e15\u0e01\u0e23\u0e2d\u0e1a \u0e0b\u0e39\u0e0b\u0e39\u0e01\u0e34 \u0e04\u0e31\u0e1e 2018|date=2018-12-06}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Manager===\n'''Thailand'''\n*[[King's Cup]]: [[2017 King's Cup|2017]]<ref>{{cite web|work=Footballghana.com|url=https://footballghana.com/ex-ghana-coach-milovan-rajevac-wins-first-silverware-with-thailand|title=Ex-Ghana coach Milovan Rajevac wins first silverware with Thailand|date=19 July 2017|accessdate=6 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Serbian Footballer of the Year|Serbian Coach of the Year]]: 2010<ref>{{cite web|work=Blic Sport|url=https://sport.blic.rs/fudbal/domaci-fudbal/fss-stankovic-i-rajevac-najbolji-u-2010-godini/jen95r6|title=FSS: Stankovi\u0107 i Rajevac najbolji u 2010. godini|date=23 December 2018|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref>\n*[[CAF Awards|African Coach of the Year]]: 2010<ref>{{cite web|work=Ahram Online|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/6/52/20336/Sports/National-Teams/Serbian-coach-Rajevac-joins-race-for-Egypt-job.aspx|title=Serbian coach Rajevac joins race for Egypt job|date=5 September 2011|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Milovan Rajevac international tournaments\n|list1=\n{{Ghana Squad 2010 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Ghana Squad 2010 World Cup}}\n{{Thailand squad 2019 AFC Asian Cup}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Milovan Rajevac managerial positions\n|list1=\n{{Red Star Belgrade managers}}\n{{FK Vojvodina managers}}\n{{Ghana national football team managers}}\n{{Al-Ahli Saudi FC managers}}\n{{Qatar national football team managers}}\n{{Algeria national football team managers}}\n{{Thailand national football team managers}}\n}}\n{{Football Association of Serbia Coach of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rajevac, Milovan}}\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from \u010cajetina]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav footballers]]\n[[Category:Serbian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak players]]\n[[Category:Red Star Belgrade footballers]]\n[[Category:FK Vojvodina players]]\n[[Category:FK Sloboda U\u017eice players]]\n[[Category:Serbian football managers]]\n[[Category:Red Star Belgrade managers]]\n[[Category:FK Vojvodina managers]]\n[[Category:2010 FIFA World Cup managers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Ghana]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Qatar]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Serbian SuperLiga managers]]\n[[Category:Serbian people of Bosnia and Herzegovina descent]]\n[[Category:Al-Ahli Saudi FC managers]]\n[[Category:Ghana national football team managers]]\n[[Category:Qatar national football team managers]]\n[[Category:FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak managers]]\n[[Category:FK Sloboda U\u017eice managers]]\n[[Category:NK Rudar Velenje managers]]\n[[Category:Serbian expatriates in Slovenia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Slovenia]]\n[[Category:2010 Africa Cup of Nations managers]]\n[[Category:Algeria national football team managers]]\n[[Category:Thailand national football team managers]]\n[[Category:2019 AFC Asian Cup managers]]\n", "name_user": "Benica11", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eManagerial career:Grammar", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milovan_Rajevac"}
{"title_page": "Vasyl Novokhatsky", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Vasyl Novokhatskyi\n| image = \n| fullname = Vasyl Novokhatskyi\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1974|9|24|df=yes}}\n| birth_place =[[Kalynivka, Vinnytsia Oblast]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.80}}\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber = \n| position = Midfielder\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 1992 | clubs1 = [[PFC Nyva Vinnytsia|Nyva Vinnytsia]] | caps1 = 8 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 1993\u20131994 | clubs2 = [[FC CSKA Kyiv|CSKA Kyiv]] | caps2 = 52 | goals2 = 9\n| years3 = 1995 | clubs3 = [[FC Arsenal Kyiv|CSKA-Borysfen Kyiv]] | caps3 = 11 | goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 1995\u20131996 | clubs4 = [[Ionikos F.C.|Ionikos]] | caps4 = 31 | goals4 = 10\n| years5 = 1996\u20131997 | clubs5 = [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa]] | caps5 = 9 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 1997\u20131998 | clubs6 = [[Panachaiki]] | caps6 = 25 | goals6 = 4\n| years7 = 1998\u20131999 | clubs7 = [[FC Arsenal Kyiv|CSKA Kyiv]] | caps7 = 7 | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 1998\u20131999 | clubs8 = \u2192 [[FC CSKA Kyiv|CSKA-2 Kyiv]] ''(loan)''| caps8 = 15 | goals8 = 1\n| years9 = 2001\u20132002 | clubs9 = [[Chania F.C.|Chania]] | caps9 = | goals9 = \n| years10= 2010\u20132011 | clubs10= SC Kalynivka | caps10= 11 | goals10= 1\n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| manageryears1 = | managerclubs1 =  \n| pcupdate = \n| ntupdate =\n}}\n'''Vasyl Novokhatskyi''' ({{lang-ua|\u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0445\u0430\u0446\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439}}; born 24 september 1974) is a retired [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] for clubs in Ukraine, Greece, and Israel. His last name often is misspelled as Novohatsky ({{lang-ua|\u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u0430\u0446\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439}}), because of a [[transliteration]] inconsistency.\n\n==Club career==\nNovokhatskyi began playing football for [[Ukrainian Premier League]] side [[PFC Nyva Vinnytsia]]. Soon, he joined [[FC CSKA Kyiv]], and would score a goal as the club lost the [[1997\u201398 Ukrainian Cup]] final.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=\"Den\"|script-title=uk:\u0413\u0456\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043c'\u0454\u0440\u0430 \u0426\u0421\u041a\u0410 \u0432 \u0434\u0435\u043d\u044c \u0442\u0440\u0435\u0442\u044c\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0443 \u0414\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043c\u043e|author1=Marusenko, Petro  |author2=Karelskyi, Evhen |lastauthoramp=yes |url=http://www.day.kiev.ua/142222/|language=Ukrainian|date=2 June 1998}}</ref>\n\nIn July 1995, Novokhatskyi joined [[Greek Superleague]] side [[Ionikos F.C.]] for the one season. He spent the following season with [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.]] before returning to Greece to play for [[Panachaiki|Panachaiki F.C.]] for one season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|author=Mastrogiannopoulos, Alexander|title=Foreign Players in Greece since 1959/60|url=http://www.rsssf.com/players/foreign-players-in-grk6080.html|date=11 May 2005}}</ref>\n\nHe played for [[Gamma Ethniki|Greek third division]] side [[Chania F.C.]] during the 2001\u201302 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=epae.org|title=\u03a0\u03c1\u03c9\u03c4\u03ac\u03b8\u03bb\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 / FOOTBALL LEAGUE 2 / \u03a0\u03a1\u03a9\u03a4\u0391\u0398\u039b\u0397\u039c\u0391 \u0393 ' \u0395\u0398\u039d\u0399\u039a\u0397\u03a3 \u039a\u0391\u03a4\u0397\u0393\u039f\u03a1\u0399\u0391\u03a3 2001-2002 / 1\u03b7 \u03b1\u03b3\u03c9\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae / \u039c\u0391\u03a1\u039a\u039f \u039c\u0391\u03a1\u039a\u039f\u03a0\u039f\u03a5\u039b\u039f\u03a5 \u0393\u03a3 \u03a0\u0391\u0395 - \u03a7\u0391\u039d\u0399\u0391 \u0391.\u039f. \u03a0\u0391\u0395|url=http://www.epae.org/match.fds?categ=3&dior_code=53&cal_day=1&game=3&group=0&type=1&pagecode=01.03&langid=1|language=Greek|date=3 October 2001}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{FFU Profile|25852}}\n*[http://legioner.kulichki.com/index.php?id=11&lang=en&player=312 Profile at legioner.kulichki.com]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110724033111/http://www.axaioi3.gr/forum/index.php?topic=133.0 \u039e\u0395\u039d\u039f\u0399 \u03a0\u0391\u0399\u039a\u03a4\u0395\u03a3 \u039a\u0391\u0399 \u03a0\u03a1\u039f\u03a0\u039f\u039d\u0397\u03a4\u0395\u03a3 \u03a4\u0397\u03a3 \u03a0\u0391\u039d\u0391\u03a7\u0391\u03aa\u039a\u0397\u03a3]\n\n{{use dmy dates|date=September 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Novokhatskyi, Vasyl}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Kalynivka]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Nyva Vinnytsia players]]\n[[Category:FC Dnipro Cherkasy players]]\n[[Category:FC CSKA Kyiv players]]\n[[Category:FC Arsenal Kyiv players]]\n[[Category:Ionikos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Panachaiki F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Maccabi Haifa F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian military personnel of the War in Donbass]]\n\n\n{{Ukraine-footy-midfielder-1970s-stub}}\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Vasyl Novokhatskyi\n| image = \n| fullname = Vasyl Novokhatskyi\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1974|4|29|df=yes}}\n| birth_place =[[Kalynivka, Vinnytsia Oblast]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.90}}\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber = \n| position = Midfielder\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 1992 | clubs1 = [[PFC Nyva Vinnytsia|Nyva Vinnytsia]] | caps1 = 8 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 1993\u20131994 | clubs2 = [[FC CSKA Kyiv|CSKA Kyiv]] | caps2 = 52 | goals2 = 9\n| years3 = 1995 | clubs3 = [[FC Arsenal Kyiv|CSKA-Borysfen Kyiv]] | caps3 = 11 | goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 1995\u20131996 | clubs4 = [[Ionikos F.C.|Ionikos]] | caps4 = 31 | goals4 = 10\n| years5 = 1996\u20131997 | clubs5 = [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa]] | caps5 = 9 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 1997\u20131998 | clubs6 = [[Panachaiki]] | caps6 = 25 | goals6 = 4\n| years7 = 1998\u20131999 | clubs7 = [[FC Arsenal Kyiv|CSKA Kyiv]] | caps7 = 7 | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 1998\u20131999 | clubs8 = \u2192 [[FC CSKA Kyiv|CSKA-2 Kyiv]] ''(loan)''| caps8 = 15 | goals8 = 1\n| years9 = 2001\u20132002 | clubs9 = [[Chania F.C.|Chania]] | caps9 = | goals9 = \n| years10= 2010\u20132011 | clubs10= SC Kalynivka | caps10= 11 | goals10= 1\n| nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = \n| manageryears1 = | managerclubs1 =  \n| pcupdate = \n| ntupdate =\n}}\n'''Vasyl Novokhatskyi''' ({{lang-ua|\u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0445\u0430\u0446\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439}}; born 24 september 1974) is a retired [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] for clubs in Ukraine, Greece, and Israel. His last name often is misspelled as Novohatsky ({{lang-ua|\u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u0430\u0446\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439}}), because of a [[transliteration]] inconsistency.\n\n==Club career==\nNovokhatskyi began playing football for [[Ukrainian Premier League]] side [[PFC Nyva Vinnytsia]]. Soon, he joined [[FC CSKA Kyiv]], and would score a goal as the club lost the [[1997\u201398 Ukrainian Cup]] final.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=\"Den\"|script-title=uk:\u0413\u0456\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043c'\u0454\u0440\u0430 \u0426\u0421\u041a\u0410 \u0432 \u0434\u0435\u043d\u044c \u0442\u0440\u0435\u0442\u044c\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0443 \u0414\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043c\u043e|author1=Marusenko, Petro  |author2=Karelskyi, Evhen |lastauthoramp=yes |url=http://www.day.kiev.ua/142222/|language=Ukrainian|date=2 June 1998}}</ref>\n\nIn July 1995, Novokhatskyi joined [[Greek Superleague]] side [[Ionikos F.C.]] for the one season. He spent the following season with [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.]] before returning to Greece to play for [[Panachaiki|Panachaiki F.C.]] for one season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|author=Mastrogiannopoulos, Alexander|title=Foreign Players in Greece since 1959/60|url=http://www.rsssf.com/players/foreign-players-in-grk6080.html|date=11 May 2005}}</ref>\n\nHe played for [[Gamma Ethniki|Greek third division]] side [[Chania F.C.]] during the 2001\u201302 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=epae.org|title=\u03a0\u03c1\u03c9\u03c4\u03ac\u03b8\u03bb\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 / FOOTBALL LEAGUE 2 / \u03a0\u03a1\u03a9\u03a4\u0391\u0398\u039b\u0397\u039c\u0391 \u0393 ' \u0395\u0398\u039d\u0399\u039a\u0397\u03a3 \u039a\u0391\u03a4\u0397\u0393\u039f\u03a1\u0399\u0391\u03a3 2001-2002 / 1\u03b7 \u03b1\u03b3\u03c9\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae / \u039c\u0391\u03a1\u039a\u039f \u039c\u0391\u03a1\u039a\u039f\u03a0\u039f\u03a5\u039b\u039f\u03a5 \u0393\u03a3 \u03a0\u0391\u0395 - \u03a7\u0391\u039d\u0399\u0391 \u0391.\u039f. \u03a0\u0391\u0395|url=http://www.epae.org/match.fds?categ=3&dior_code=53&cal_day=1&game=3&group=0&type=1&pagecode=01.03&langid=1|language=Greek|date=3 October 2001}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{FFU Profile|25852}}\n*[http://legioner.kulichki.com/index.php?id=11&lang=en&player=312 Profile at legioner.kulichki.com]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110724033111/http://www.axaioi3.gr/forum/index.php?topic=133.0 \u039e\u0395\u039d\u039f\u0399 \u03a0\u0391\u0399\u039a\u03a4\u0395\u03a3 \u039a\u0391\u0399 \u03a0\u03a1\u039f\u03a0\u039f\u039d\u0397\u03a4\u0395\u03a3 \u03a4\u0397\u03a3 \u03a0\u0391\u039d\u0391\u03a7\u0391\u03aa\u039a\u0397\u03a3]\n\n{{use dmy dates|date=September 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Novokhatskyi, Vasyl}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Kalynivka]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Nyva Vinnytsia players]]\n[[Category:FC Dnipro Cherkasy players]]\n[[Category:FC CSKA Kyiv players]]\n[[Category:FC Arsenal Kyiv players]]\n[[Category:Ionikos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Panachaiki F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Maccabi Haifa F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian military personnel of t